    <description>
      BigFloat is a high-precision floating-point arithmetic library implemented in C#. 
      It provides arbitrary-precision floating-point numbers with a dynamically sized 
      mantissa, optimized algorithms, and no external dependencies. Suitable for scientific, 
      engineering, and financial applications requiring precise numeric computation.
    </description>

    <summary>
      High-performance arbitrary-precision floating-point arithmetic for .NET.
    </summary>

<releaseNotes>
  See https://github.com/SunsetQuest/BigFloat/releases/tag/v4.2.0
  for detailed release notes, breaking changes, and migration guidance.
</releaseNotes>

